					<head>Commentary</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597" rend="visible">
						<summary>A fragment of Judeo-Arabic commentary of Japheth ben Ali ha-Levi on Numbers (22-36).</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he" otherLangs="jrb">Hebrew, Judeo-Arabic</textLang>
						<msItem n="0" rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597">
							<locus from="1r" to="130v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Perush Be-midbar</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">פרוש במדבר</title>
							<note>
								<p>The unpointed text of Ex. 22:2-24:14, 24:18-27:1, 27:9-31:20, 31:23-53, 32:6-35:34, 36:5-13 is embodied, followed by the Arabic translation.</p>
							</note>
							<author key="http://viaf.org/viaf/54984961">
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/54984961" xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Japheth ben Ali, ha-Levi,‏ active 10th century </persName>
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/54984961" xml:lang="he">יפת בן עלי, הלוי</persName>
							</author>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of the 16th to 17th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper codex.</support>
								<extent>130 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>210</height>
										<width>150</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>170</height>
										<width>115</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>130 folios (+ 2 paper flyleaves at the beginning and at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>13 quires (1-3 and 3-12) of mostly 10 leaves each.</p>
									<p>Quires signed with Hebrew letters and Arabic words on the upper margin of the first page, and with Hebrew letters on the lower margin of the last page.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Imperfect, with lacunae after folio 27, 47, 87, 93 and 123.</p>
									<p>Water-damaged.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="21" writtenLines="21">
									<p>The Hebrew biblical text is embodied.</p>
									<p>Catchword on every verso.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Semi-cursive script of 16th to 17th century.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>Folios 127r-128r supply the contents of the missing leaf after folio 123.</p>
						</additions>
